<br>
    If anyone doesn't mind might I ask a few questions? I am a ex DAoC and ex EQ player and was thinking of coming back to EQ but rather then going back to Innoruuk I was thinking of this server (haven't gotten a account yet still debating) I played here on FV when it first started  but became rather tired of the lack of rping (no flame intended) and I was just wondering how the Roleplaying on this server is going? Well thats it for now.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upentapod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentapod</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/graphics/a_pod.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>WTB phat newt</span><br>  Posts: 984<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/18/02 10:37:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=205.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/miscpics/couple.jpg height=200 width=100.gif></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings and Well met</span><hr size=1> Well!  It depends on who you ask, and there are LONG and heated debates on the topic.<br>
<br>
I guess most would say the roleplaying here is still much better than it is on the other servers.<br>
<br>
But, not as good as it was pre-May patch, which relaxed a lot of our tougher rules.<br>
<br>
You will likely also find that roleplaying under 20 is harder to find, due to a flood of young players who haven't been either discouraged from playing here or converted to roleplayers.  Best roleplaying will be in the 20-50 rank range, I think.  Your race also makes a difference ... much more likely to find roleplaying in Ak'Anon than you are in Kelethin, in my experience.<br>
<br>
There's still a lot of great roleplayers around and the server has developed some wonderful legends (Shintou ... Gore ...) and history (The Battle of Ak'Anon ... the Kidnapping of Ellishae...)<br>
<br>
At the end of the day, you'll have to stick around and decide for yourself what you think!  I recommend browsing around the guilds and associations area and finding some RP guilds/associations you like the sound of, then lurk in their chat channels to find other like-minded roleplayers, even before you are ready to join a guild.  (Channels like TheLoSBar, Joybringers, DreadGnomePirates, etc. spring to mind)<br>
<br>
And, of course, lurk around these boards, make yourself at home (just ignore the flames and screams crackling behind the doors of the soapbox, that's the brawling area...) and I hope we'll see you in Norrath!<br>
<br>
Didi<br>
