<br>
The classes are also balanced ok.  Maybe see a few less clerics, magicians, shamans, and beastlords then others.  Beccause the server population is low, there are more people playing classes that can solo.  But i do have to say there are too many paladins, rangers, and shadowknights around.  I am really enjoying being a wizard.  <br>
<br>
Races is where it's uneven.  Theres elves coming out our ears, dark, high, and wood.  Also lots of humans and quite a lot of lizards.  There are never enough gnomes!  Also the ugly races - trolls, ogres, dwarves, halflings.  You probably meet more roleplayers playing ugly races, because they not just playing them to look pretty.  I think.<br>
<br>
If you want to play something unusual, a Bertoxxulous worshipper maybe?  (There is a new Bertoxxulous-only guild called Cult of the Plaguebringer now.)  An Erudian tank of some kind?  Gnome shadow knights and paladins are still pretty rare too, since they became allowed classes for gnomes.  Ask yourself what do you enjoy playing?<br>
